data.text: @James96413396 @chiproytx @RepThomasMassie @RepJohnRose You reveal your ignorance - and complete lack of compassion  - in your response. The debate regards emergency Federal relief funding - received by every single other area hit by a hurricane for decades, usually within 30 days, we're past 200. You're embarrassing yourself.

Week one, and @Goodrick_Jake, @PeterNicieja and I have travelled to Panama City (for work, I swear) to look into disaster fraud and some other aftermath from Hurricane Michael. Tomorrow, we’ll be hearing from experts on insurance fraud at a town hall in prep for hurricane season https://t.co/dx2snwq4SC

Tiny chance of a shower or storm later today, but it’s been a beautiful couple of days in Panama City Beach, FL. 

We’re talking about Hurricane Michael recovery along the Panhandle on @WeatherNation as Atlantic hurricane season starts tomorrow. https://t.co/8NbZLz5EHO
@KathrynProciv Cancelled my flight home for a 1 day rest and headed straight to Fla for the start of Hurricane season....a little birdy named KP warned me travel into Newark might be rough tonight.
